# Flask Simple Web App

A simple Flask web application that displays an input form and returns the submitted text. The project uses a `src/` directory structure and a Python virtual environment.


## Requirements

- Python 3.10+
- pip
- PowerShell or CMD (Windows)
- Git (optional)

## Project Structure

│
├── venv/ # Virtual environment (ignored by Git)
├── src/
│ └── app.py # Main Flask application
│
└── .gitignore

## Setup Instructions (Windows)

### 1. Create virtual environment

```powershell
python -m venv venv
2. Activate virtual environment

PowerShell:

.\venv\Scripts\Activate


If script execution is blocked:

Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope CurrentUser -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned

3. Install Flask
pip install Flask

Running the Application
Option 1: Run directly
python src/app.py

Option 2: Using flask run
$env:FLASK_APP="src/app.py"
flask run
The app will be available at:
http://127.0.0.1:5000/